{"id": 5723, "date": "1987-02-02T11:00:42", "date_gmt": "1987-02-02T19:00:42", "guid": {"rendered": "http://estreetshuffle.com/?p=5723"}, "modified": "2026-06-08T13:32:02", "modified_gmt": "2026-06-08T20:32:02", "slug": "matr-bruce-springsteen-midnight-thunder-and-southside-johnny-keep-knockin", "status": "publish", "type": "post", "link": "https://estreetshuffle.com/index.php/1987/02/02/matr-bruce-springsteen-midnight-thunder-and-southside-johnny-keep-knockin/", "title": {"rendered": "Keep A-Knockin&#8217;"}, "content": {"rendered": "<p>Some songs get passed down from generation to generation, with one artist inspiring the next.</p>\n<p>&#8220;Keep A-Knockin&#8221; was first recorded by blues artist James Wiggins in 1928&#8230;</p>\n<div class=\"jetpack-video-wrapper\"><span class=\"embed-youtube\" style=\"text-align:center; display: block;\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" class=\"youtube-player\" width=\"758\" height=\"427\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/cPYeXbc8rns?version=3&#038;rel=1&#038;showsearch=0&#038;showinfo=1&#038;iv_load_policy=1&#038;fs=1&#038;hl=en-US&#038;autohide=2&#038;wmode=transparent\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" style=\"border:0;\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation allow-popups-to-escape-sandbox\"></iframe></span></div>\n<p>&#8230;which inspired Louis Jordan to cut a smoother take on it in 1939&#8230;</p>\n<div class=\"jetpack-video-wrapper\"><span class=\"embed-youtube\" style=\"text-align:center; display: block;\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" class=\"youtube-player\" width=\"758\" height=\"427\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/6pcve7daxNM?version=3&#038;rel=1&#038;showsearch=0&#038;showinfo=1&#038;iv_load_policy=1&#038;fs=1&#038;hl=en-US&#038;autohide=2&#038;wmode=transparent\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" style=\"border:0;\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation allow-popups-to-escape-sandbox\"></iframe></span></div>\n<p>&#8230;which in turn inspired Louis Jordan fan Little Richard to turn it into an uptempo stomp rocker in 1957.</p>\n<div class=\"jetpack-video-wrapper\"><span class=\"embed-youtube\" style=\"text-align:center; display: block;\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" class=\"youtube-player\" width=\"758\" height=\"427\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/FuvQ4ag4X5g?version=3&#038;rel=1&#038;showsearch=0&#038;showinfo=1&#038;iv_load_policy=1&#038;fs=1&#038;hl=en-US&#038;autohide=2&#038;wmode=transparent\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" style=\"border:0;\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation allow-popups-to-escape-sandbox\"></iframe></span></div>\n<p>And it&#8217;s Little Richard&#8217;s version that undoubtedly inspired Bruce&#8217;s only known performances.\u00a0Bruce took a swing at it three times in the 1980s, all at club performances, and all with other artists.</p>\n<p>The first time was at The Stone Pony with Cats on a Smooth Surface in July 1983&#8211;but unfortunately no audio of that performance has surfaced. A week later, though, Bruce covered it with Midnight Thunder at The Headline in nearby Neptune, and we are lucky to have\u00a0<em>that</em> recording in soundboard clarity.</p>\n<div class=\"jetpack-video-wrapper\"><span class=\"embed-youtube\" style=\"text-align:center; display: block;\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" class=\"youtube-player\" width=\"758\" height=\"427\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/HLTYWRfvc-U?version=3&#038;rel=1&#038;showsearch=0&#038;showinfo=1&#038;iv_load_policy=1&#038;fs=1&#038;hl=en-US&#038;autohide=2&#038;wmode=transparent\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" style=\"border:0;\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation allow-popups-to-escape-sandbox\"></iframe></span></div>\n<p>Five years later, Bruce took one final (to date) run at &#8220;Keep A-Knockin'&#8221; &#8212; this time with Southside Johnny and The Asbury Jukes at The Stone in San Francisco over Thanksgiving weekend, 1988. It&#8217;s a short performance (it segued into &#8220;Little Queenie&#8221;) but a fun one, and you can hear it below.</p>\n<div class=\"jetpack-video-wrapper\"><span class=\"embed-youtube\" style=\"text-align:center; display: block;\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" class=\"youtube-player\" width=\"758\" height=\"427\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/ZRShCBKt9Vs?version=3&#038;rel=1&#038;showsearch=0&#038;showinfo=1&#038;iv_load_policy=1&#038;fs=1&#038;hl=en-US&#038;autohide=2&#038;wmode=transparent\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" style=\"border:0;\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation allow-popups-to-escape-sandbox\"></iframe></span></div>\n<p><strong>Keep A-Knockin&#8217;<br />\nFirst performed:</strong> July 10, 1983 (Asbury Park, NJ)<br />\n<strong>Last performed:</strong> November 26, 1988 (San Francisco, CA)</p>\n<p>\u00a9 November 9, 2018</p>\n", "protected": false}, "excerpt": {"rendered": "<p>Bruce took a few runs at Little Richard&#8217;s &#8220;Keep A-Knockin&#8217;.&#8221; Listen to two of them here: one with Midnight Thunder, the other with Southside Johnny and The Asbury Jukes.</p>\n", "protected": false}, "author": 1, "featured_media": 69732, "comment_status": "open", "ping_status": "open", "sticky": false, "template": "", "format": "standard", "meta": {"_monsterinsights_skip_tracking": false, "_monsterinsights_sitenote_active": false, "_monsterinsights_sitenote_note": "", "_monsterinsights_sitenote_category": 0, "_jetpack_newsletter_access": "", "_jetpack_dont_email_post_to_subs": false, "_jetpack_newsletter_tier_id": 0, "_jetpack_memberships_contains_paywalled_content": false, "_jetpack_feature_clip_id": 0, "_jetpack_memberships_contains_paid_content": false, "footnotes": "", "jetpack_publicize_message": "", "jetpack_publicize_feature_enabled": true, "jetpack_social_post_already_shared": true, "jetpack_social_options": {"image_generator_settings": {"template": "highway", "default_image_id": 0, "font": "", "enabled": false}, "version": 2}, "jetpack_post_was_ever_publishe